page.title: 07ECOLOGY 1
page.content: We are very lucky where we live because there is a canal and lots of fields, countryside and farms. When we went on our 5 mile sponsored Domesday walk around our area we saw lots of living things as we passed through the streets and countryside. There were buttercups on the side of the road and wild iris inbetween tall reeds growing by the canal. Earthnuts or pignuts were growing practically everywhere. There were daisies, dandelions and wild bluebells scattered along the grass verges and dock leaves and berries in the hedges. I saw lots of cabbage white butterflies and a caterpillar on a leaf with a ladybird which was preparing to fly. There were lots of brambles and nettles hanging into the road and bees and wasps were hovering over various wild flowers.
